summaries.short: Thackery's connection to Captain Robertson is revealed; Algernon's conflict with Gallinger comes to a head.
summaries.full: Thackery's connection to Captain Robertson, and how the doctor arrived at the Knick, is revealed. The conflict between Algernon and Gallinger comes to a head. Cleary and Harriet launch a joint-business venture; Lucy shares memories with her father; Barrow confronts the rising costs of living well; Cornelia and Henry weigh the cost of a family crisis.

summaries.short: Eric Johnson (Dr. Everett Gallinger) delves into his character’s development with Michael Angarano and hosts Jack Amiel and Michael Begler.
summaries.full: Eric Johnson (Dr. Everett Gallinger) delves into his character’s development with Michael Angarano and hosts Jack Amiel and Michael Begler.

summaries.short: Season Two Finale. Thackery performs his most dramatic operation ever; Cornelia and Henry weigh their futures following a family revelation.
summaries.full: Season Two Finale. Thackery eschews Zinberg's advice at Mt. Sinai and opts for a dramatic, and risky, alternative course of action. Cornelia and Henry weigh their futures following an alarming family revelation; Barrow defends his actions at the hospital construction site; Gallinger considers a job opportunity; Cleary refuses to give up on Harriet.

summaries.short: Thackery faces the realities of his addiction research; Gallinger shuffles his family priorities.
summaries.full: After dealing with an unwanted intruder, Thackery faces the realities of his addiction research, and sets his sights on improving Abby's appearance. Algernon suspects foul play during his surgical debacle; Gallinger shuffles his family priorities; Barrow's social standing rises, at a cost; Lucy makes a shocking discovery; Cornelia shares unsettling news with Henry.

summaries.short: Hosts Jack Amiel and Michael Begler break down episode ten with Michael Angarano; plus, Andre Holland reflects on the first two seasons.
summaries.full: Hosts Jack Amiel and Michael Begler break down episode ten with Michael Angarano; plus, Andre Holland reflects on the first two seasons.

summaries.short: Emmy(R) award winning costume designer Ellen Mirojnik goes through her process, from sketch idea to the fitting room.
summaries.full: Emmy(R) award winning costume designer Ellen Mirojnik goes through her process, from sketch idea to the fitting room.

summaries.short: Thackery faces a daunting surgery; a charity ball is held for the new Knick; Algernon has an opportunity to shine in the surgical theater.
summaries.full: Fighting his nerves, Thackery readies himself to attempt to separate Zoya and Nika in front of a packed audience. After getting a surprise gift from her father-in-law, Cornelia attends a gala charity ball for the new Knick with other familiar guests. Barrow gets rid of a threat; Opal spoils the Robertsons' good mood. Algernon gets an overdue spotlight in the surgical theater.

summaries.short: Chris Sullivan and Michael Angarano discuss the ins and outs of filming episode 7; later, dolly grip Mike Morini joins the conversation.
summaries.full: Chris Sullivan and Michael Angarano discuss the ins and outs of filming episode 7; later, dolly grip Mike Morini joins the conversation.

summaries.short: Bertie takes matters into his own hands at Mt. Sinai; Thackery takes an interest in a pair of conjoined twins.
summaries.full: Faced with a quandary, Bertie decides to take matters into his own hands at Mt. Sinai, enlisting Algernon to help. Thackery investigates the efficacy of hypnosis, and takes an interest in a pair of conjoined twins. Lucy lobbies Henry for a gala invitation; Cornelia visits the brother of a deceased immigrant with ties to Speight; Gallinger dines with an unwelcome guest.

summaries.short: Emmy(R)-winning production designer Howard Cummings takes listeners behind the scenes of Huber's Palace, the surgical theater and more.
summaries.full: Emmy(R)-winning production designer Howard Cummings takes listeners behind the scenes of Huber's Palace, the surgical theater and more.
